Lagos – The controversies that have been trailing the Alliance for New Nigeria (ANN) has been put to rest following the Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) recognition of Mr. Fela Durotoye as the presidential candidate of the party. A statement signed by the director-general of the ANN presidential campaign team said Durotoye’s name was in the list of presidential candidates, whose particulars were published by the electoral umpire. The team said the announcement officially ended all doubts about the position of Durotoye as the presidential candidate of the party “against the numerous propagandas and allegations invented by the enemies of this great party.” It called on Mr. Gbenga Olawepo-Hashim, who it accused of peddling confusion in the media and amongst the public about the true presidential candidate of the party after organizing a counterfeit primary is now listed as the Presidential candidate of People’s Trust.”